@startuml ConnectifyAI Activity Diagram
!theme plain
title Connectify AI — User Activity Flow

actor User
participant "Frontend (React)" as FE
participant "API (Django)" as API
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "AI Services" as AI
participant "WebSocket (Chat)" as WS

== User Registration & Login ==
User -> FE: Open App
FE -> API: GET / (check auth)
API --> FE: 401 / redirect to login
User -> FE: Submit Register/Login
FE -> API: POST /register or /login
API -> DB: Create/Validate User
DB --> API: User record
API --> FE: JWT tokens
FE -> FE: Store tokens, update AuthContext

== Upload Video & Generate Captions ==
User -> FE: Go to AI Caption Generator
FE -> API: POST /videos/upload (multipart)
API -> DB: Create Video (status=uploading)
API --> FE: Video ID
FE -> AI: Start upload progress
API -> DB: Update Video status=processing
API -> AI: Trigger Caption Job (Async)
AI -> DB: Create CaptionProcessingJob
AI -> AI: AssemblyAI / Whisper
AI -> DB: Save Caption rows, update Job status
API -> DB: Update Video status=ready
FE -> API: GET /videos/{id}/ (poll status)
API --> FE: Video + Captions

== Publish Video with Captions ==
User -> FE: Click "Publish with Captions"
FE -> API: PATCH /videos/{id}/ (caption_enabled, language_mode)
API -> DB: Update Video caption settings
FE -> API: POST /videos/{id}/publish/
API -> DB: Video.publish() → Create Post + PostMedia (copy captions)
DB --> API: Post + PostMedia
API --> FE: 201 Created
FE -> FE: Navigate to Feed

== View Feed (Posts) ==
User -> FE: Open Feed
FE -> API: GET /posts/ (paginated)
API -> DB: Fetch Posts + Media + Likes + Comments
DB --> API: List of Posts
API --> FE: Serialized Posts
FE -> FE: Render PostCard(s)
FE -> FE: Generate VTT from PostMedia.captions (if video)
FE -> FE: Attach <track> to <video> or render overlay

== Like / Comment on Post ==
User -> FE: Click Like
FE -> API: POST /posts/{id}/like/
API -> DB: Create Like (unique)
API --> FE: 201
FE -> FE: Update UI optimistically

User -> FE: Submit Comment
FE -> API: POST /posts/{id}/comments/
API -> AI: Optional toxicity/sentiment analysis
AI --> API: Scores
API -> DB: Create Comment with AI fields
API --> FE: Serialized Comment
FE -> FE: Append to Comment list

== Real‑time Chat ==
User -> FE: Open Messages
FE -> API: GET /chat/threads/
API -> DB: Threads where user is participant
DB --> API: Threads list
API --> FE: Threads
User -> FE: Select Thread
FE -> API: GET /chat/threads/{id}/messages/
API -> DB: Messages for thread
DB --> API: Messages
API --> FE: Messages
FE -> WS: Connect ws://.../ws/chat/{threadId}/?token=jwt
WS -> FE: Authenticated
User -> FE: Send Message (text/image/video/audio)
FE -> API: POST /chat/messages/
API -> DB: Create Message
API -> WS: Broadcast to thread group
WS -> FE: Push new message to all participants
FE -> FE: Render new message instantly

== Delete Post ==
User -> FE: Click Delete (if owner)
FE -> FE: Show ConfirmationModal
User -> FE: Confirm
FE -> API: DELETE /posts/{id}/
API -> DB: Delete Post (cascade media/likes/comments)
API --> FE: 204
FE -> FE: Remove Post from UI, show toast

== AI Caption Translation (Optional) ==
User -> FE: Select Language & Translate
FE -> API: POST /videos/{id}/translate/
API -> AI: Translate Captions
AI -> DB: Create translated Caption rows
API --> FE: Updated captions
FE -> FE: Re-render captions in new language

@enduml
